Commentary: full, 120kph and diving in from outside off stump as Guptill has a yahoo and misses
Commentary_short: SM Curran to Guptill, no run

Commentary: smashed off a length, easy-paced from Curran and Guptill rocks back and belabours a pull over midwicket and away! First runs of the day
Commentary_short: SM Curran to Guptill, FOUR runs

Commentary: shortish, 124kph/77mph and again Guptill frees the arms, hacks an inside edge through square leg
drops a little short again, Munro charges down and whips a pull past midwicket, not completely timed and Tom Curran runs gingerly after it
short and wide, maybe a slower delivery... splatted over the infield for four more! Almost carries all the way to the cover boundary, as Munro tucked in
Commentary_short: SM Curran to Munro, FOUR runs

Commentary: pitched up, in the slot and crunched down the ground for six! First one of the day, just a lofted drive from Munro and it carries easily beyond the rope at long-on. Might see a few more of those...
Commentary_short: SM Curran to Munro, SIX runs

Commentary: short of a length, slower delivery and heaved away, again not quite timed but gets it in front of deep midwicket for four
Commentary_short: TK Curran to Guptill, FOUR runs

Commentary: length ball, pace off... and pace back on at a rate of knots! Smeared into the crowd at deep midwicket, bat swinging like a meat cleaver. Oof!
Commentary_short: TK Curran to Guptill, SIX runs

Commentary: tighter line, this is swatted away through square leg for a couple more
pitched up, 134kph/83mph, nice and juicy - Blammo! Straight back down the ground and into the bleachers for six more!
Commentary_short: TK Curran to Guptill, SIX runs

Commentary: shortish outside off and Guptill carves it up and over cover point for a couple more as the fielders give chase
slower ball, mistimed on the pull towards midwicket
Commentary_short: TK Curran to Guptill, no run

Commentary: starts with a cutter, full outside off, smoked back over the rope at long-off! Munro is in the zone, moves to 18 off FOUR balls!!
shortish on the hip, settles for a punch through square on the leg side
goes full and wide, 136kph/84mph but that simply allows Guptill to open his shoulders and slap it hard through point for four
that's outta here! Babe Ruth hitting from Guptill, advancing on the bumper and hammering a pull into the top tier at deep midwicket!
fires in the yorker, around fifth stump and he sneaks it under the bat - a rare dot ball for England
pitched up, 138kph/86mph on the stumps, pinged through mid-on for a single to finish the Powerplay
flights the legbreak, swing and a miss from Guptill... and Billings whips off the bails, too, necessitating a check with the third umpire. Don't think his back foot ever left the crease, though
floated up wide of the stumps, here comes Guppy again... bludgeoned into the crowd at wide long-off! Smashed hard and flat for six more
ugh, that's filth! Full toss, 'hit me' written all over it, and that's just what Guptill does, creaming it into the top tier once again - straight back down the ground this time!
floated up, spinning a touch on leg stump as he goes to sweep, comes off the pads
that's better from Rashid, pushes through the googly and it spins through as Munro goes back and gropes at it
tossed up, Munro sweeps and gets it away past backward square leg
shortish, dug in as Guptil pulls and takes a bit of it on his thumb, single through midwicket
banged in, 134kph/83mph and top-edged over the keeper for four! Not where Munro was aiming, but they all count

hits a length, Munro swings hard across the line... did he get an inside edge? Mahmood seemed to be celebrating as Billings collected the ball, but the keeper was focused on shying at the stumps as Guptill ran through
whipped into the leg side, that takes him to his fifty - first one of those for Guptill in international cricket since the opening match of the 50-over World Cup!
short outside off, Munro attempts to ramp but doesn't connect
dug in, 136kph/84mph and swung all the way over deep backward square! More pain for the England bowlers as these two make hay

gottim, chipped to deep midwicket! Some respite for England, Rashid making the breakthrough as we approach the halfway stage. Came off the toe of the bat as Guptill aimed for the pickets once again, securely taken by Banton a few yards in from the rope
Dismissal_text: MJ Guptill c Banton b Rashid 50 (20b 3x4 5x6) SR: 250.00

Commentary: flighted, on middle and leg, Munro sweeps hard but picks out deep backwards square
tossed up on the stumps, heaved off the pads and CDG fancies two, starts to come back... but Munro isn't moving! The throw goes to the right end, but de Grandhomme sprawls home
pushed into the off side for one
tossed up, swung away in the air, bouncing out towards deep backward square
nicely flighted, dipping on middle and off, Munro can't get under it and a single into the covers ends a good over of damage limitation for England
short ball, pulled without great timing to deep midwicket
flipped over short fine leg, 137kph/85mph and he uses the pace to whip this to the rope for four

Commentary: hurls this down fast and bumpy, touch leg side but gets away with it
Commentary_short: Mahmood to de Grandhomme, no run

Commentary: dug in short, CDG clubs it but off the splice, held by Vince running in! Looked like a legcutter from Mahmood and it was completely mistimed, lobbed out towards deep midwicket - the longest part of the ground - and there's no mistake from the fielder this time
Dismissal_text: C de Grandhomme c Vince b Mahmood 6 (5b 1x4 0x6) SR: 120.00

Commentary: back of a length and swatted leg side for one

tossed up, pitching on leg and swung away
comes down and swipes across the line, just a single to deep square

pushed through quicker, jabbed into the off side

hammered down the ground! Picks the slower ball, Munro makes room and extends the arms to pepper the stands once again

goes full and straight, worked through midwicket
